{
  "texts": [
    "In both cases, Individuals 1 and 5 are treated in the first and second rounds, respectively, and outcomes are shown as columns, with color intensity representing workout activity.",
    "When 1 and 2 are friends, the influence of Individual 1 spreads through their connection, leading to stronger responses in subsequent rounds.",
    "When they are not connected, this channel is absent, and the spillover pattern weakens (see the outcomes of Individuals 2 and 7).",
    "The differences in these evolving outcome patterns reveal the presence or absence of hidden connections.",
    "In real-world experiments, networks are large and heterogeneous, and their structure is rarely observed."
  ]
}